            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "\r\nACID transactions are a foundational concept in relational databases, ensuring reliability and consistency in data operations. The acronym stands for "
        },
        {
          "type": "strong",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, and Durability",
              "position": {
                "start": {
                  "line": 4,
                  "column": 153,
                  "offset": 257
                },
                "end": {
                  "line": 4,
                  "column": 202,
                  "offset": 306
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "position": {
            "start": {
              "line": 4,
              "column": 151,
              "offset": 255
            },
            "end": {
              "line": 4,
              "column": 204,
              "offset": 308
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": ", each addressing a critical aspect of transaction management:",
          "position": {
            "start": {
              "line": 4,
              "column": 204,
              "offset": 308
            },
            "end": {
              "line": 4,
              "column": 266,
              "offset": 370
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "position": {
        "start": {
          "line": 3,
          "column": 1,
          "offset": 41
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 4,
          "column": 266,
          "offset": 370
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
